In July and August 2004, devastating floods in Bangladesh killed over 700 people and submerged 38% of the country, displacing millions.
Monsoon rains and Himalayan snowmelt have marooned 200,000 in northern Bangladesh, with major rivers expected to worsen the situation.
Landslides in Chittagong killed 126, while millions fled their homes in India, Bangladesh, and Nepal due to heavy rains.
The military is evacuating and providing relief as rivers overflow, affecting millions.
The UK has pledged aid to support relief efforts in flood-affected areas, emphasizing the urgent need for assistance.
